 The Ekiti House of Assembly on Friday congratulated Muslim faithful in the country on the commencement of the Ramadan fast. This was contained in a statement signed by the Chairman, House Committee on Media and Public Affairs, Mrs Yemisi Ayokunle, and made available to newsmen in Ado-Ekiti. The statement urged Muslims to use the opportunity of the Ramadan to pray for peaceful coexistence, love and divine intervention to curtail the COVID-19. It said the Ramadan, being one of the pillars of Islam, provided them another opportunity for reflection and genuine love toward one another. The statement reiterated the lawmakersâ€™ commitment to support and provide quality representation that would bring about development. It wished Muslims a successful month of Ramadan while calling on the people to maintain the stay-at-home order of the government to prevent the spread of the COVID-19. (NAN)